    "text": "Seventh Avenue, north across W. 26th Street, showing mainly the easterly side. Note the newly completed 21-story loft and offices structure at the N. E. corner of 27th Street. The 20-story Manufacturers Building occupies the 28th and 29th Street frontage. The Pennsylvania Hotel is the next large unit observable. At the lower left is Guffanti's Restaurant at the S. W. Corner.\n\nApril 10, 1921\n\nGift of E. M. Jenks\n",
